Second Department,

March, 1955.

(March 1, 1955.) In the Matter of Eugene F. Connaughton et al., Respondents, against Oscar M. Taylor et al., Constituting the New York State Civil Service Commission, Appellants, et al., Defendants.

Motion to dismiss appeal and for other relief denied, without costs. This determination is without prejudice to a renewal of the motion to dismiss the appeal on the argument. Present — Nolan, P. J., MacCrate, Beldock, Murphy and Ughetta, JJ. [See post, p. 1167.]
